Reads and compiles specified *.ms files. This can be used for files already compiled with include(). Scripts that then include() these files will use the updated code. The path can be a directory or file. It is executed recursively through all subdirectories. If there's a compile error in any of the files, the function will throw an exception and other scripts will continue to use the previous version of the code when included. Returns number of files recompiled.
